The driver of the autonomous vehicle applied normal braking force to come to a stop. Shortly thereafter, the autonomous test vehicle was rear-ended by a Honda -CRV. No major bodily injuries were reported from either party in the crash. Damage to the autonomous vehicle was minor;  the car had small scratches. The Honda -CRV's driver airbag was deployed and the front bumper of the car was partially hanging out of the car's body frame. Drivers from both parties exchanged information and took pictures of the damage. The passenger of the autonomous test vehicle contacted 911 approximately at 10:05 AM and requested a CHP officer on scene. The CHP officer arrived approximately 45 minutes after the initial call and took down a report. After both parties had exchanged information, the officer dismissed both parties. The Aimotive vehicle was driven manually back to the office.

When the traffic light turned green, Vehicle 2 accelerated while still in reverse toward the Pony AV.  Vehicle 2 came to a complete stop about 4 feet from the Pony AV's front bumper. Due to the encroaching city bus and the pylons on the left edge of the Waymo AV’s lane, the Waymo AV began to brake. The Waymo AV test driver disengaged autonomous mode and took control of the Waymo AV. Approximately 1 second later, the passenger vehicle behind the Waymo AV made contact with the Waymo AV’s rear bumper at approximately 27 MPH. The Waymo AV was traveling approximately 4 MPH. The Waymo AV sustained significant damage to its rear bumper, and the passenger vehicle sustained significant damage to its front bumper. The driver of the passenger vehicle and the Waymo AV test driver were transported to receive medical attention. The Waymo AV co-driver reported minor injuries but did not receive medical attention. Amended Sections 3 and 4.

The Waymo AV was traveling southbound on Scotia Avenue, a narrow road with vehicles parked on both sides, and approaching the intersection with Thornton Avenue and Bridgeview Drive. A passenger vehicle approaching from the right of the Waymo AV on eastbound Thornton Avenue made a left turn in front of the Waymo AV to head northbound on Scotia Avenue. The Waymo AV slowed to a near stop and nudged to its right in order to share the narrow road with the oncoming vehicle and then came to a stop at the stop sign as the oncoming vehicle completed its turn. At approximately 5 mph, the turning passenger vehicle made contact with Waymo AV’s sensor hardware housing on the driver side rear corner fender of the stopped Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV sustained minor damage to the sensor hardware housing (which was the reason for towing the Waymo AV) and the passenger vehicle left the scene without exchanging information.

ExtText: On August 1, 2021 at 4:48 PM PDT, a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was struck by a bicycle at Cabrillo Street and 23rd Avenue. The cyclist stayed upright and immediately rode away, continuing northbound on 23rd Avenue. The bicycle caused minor scratches and marks on the rear driver’s side bumper of the Waymo AV. The Waymo AV was operating with a driver (in the driver’s seating position), who transitioned the vehicle from autonomous to manual mode approximately 1 second before the impact occurred. At the time of impact, the Waymo AV was in manual mode.

Address: 900 Blk Howard St, San Francisco , San Francisco , CA, 94103
ExtText: A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV"), operating in autonomous mode, was traveling northbound on 5th Street and yielding to oncoming traffic before making a left turn onto westbound Howard Street. Address: 2630 Orchard Parkway, San Jose, Santa Clara, CA, 95134
ExtText: At about 11:35 am our vehicle (car 1) was waiting behind a USPS truck to make an unprotected left turn, meanwhile one other vehicle (car 2) waited behind our vehicle. Address: 1500 McAllister St., San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94115

Address: Broadway Street at Gough Street, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94109

Address: 2500 Clement St., San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94121
ExtText:

Address: 280 S 1st Street, San Jose, Santa Clara, CA, 95113
ExtText: On June 29th 2021 at approximately 2:54 PM our safety driver was driving manually down First Street ( a one way street) from San Carlos Street  on a sunny day at 20 MPH in downtown San Jose. While proceeding straight down First street, a car parallel to our vehicle initiated a sudden lane change and began moving towards our vehicle from the bus only lane at about 10 MPH. At this point, our driver held the horn down and applied the brakes.  Our driver was unable to avoid the other vehicle due to the limited amount of space between our vehicle and the other vehicle, and the side curb to the left. At this time the car was struck; collision was unavoidable. During this time, our driver was approached by the occupants of the vehicle and information was exchanged. They said they were going to back up into the parking lot as security said they couldn't stop there. Our driver attempted to back up but due to a grinding noise, stopped. At this point our driver went to continue to get information but the occupants walked off and he couldn't abandon the vehicle.  There was moderate damage to our vehicle on the front bumper and passenger side wheel well in the form of deep dents and a small portion of the passenger side front bumper detached.  The glass covering the passenger side headlight was damaged as well.  The other vehicle sustained minor damage on the driver side front wheel well in the form of dents.

Address: McAllister Street and Larkin Street, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94102
ExtText: A Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) was traveling in manual mode at the intersection of McAllister Street and Larkin Street in San Francisco when it was involved in a collision. The Waymo AV was initially traveling eastbound on McAllister Street in autonomous mode, approaching the intersection at Larkin Street. When the Waymo AV reached the near-side crosswalk in the dedicated left turn lane, it came to a complete stop at the red traffic light. When the traffic light turned green, the Waymo AV moved forward slightly, partially entering the crosswalk, to begin staging for the turn, yielding to oncoming traffic and other road users. While waiting for an adequate clearance in traffic, the traffic light turned yellow. The Waymo AV remained stopped, declining to proceed into the intersection and make the left turn. While the AV was still stopped, the test driver took over manual control and proceeded to make the left turn. About 4 seconds later, the manually driven Waymo AV made contact with an individual riding a motorized scooter who had entered the crosswalk from the sidewalk at about 10 MPH against both vehicle and pedestrian traffic signals. The motorized scooter was traveling about 6 MPH and the Waymo AV was traveling about 7 MPH at the time of contact. The Waymo AV sustained minor damage to its front license plate. The individual on the motorized scooter appeared to have sustained unknown soft tissue injuries, but left the scene independently.

Address: Euclid Avenue at Collins Street, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94118
ExtText: A Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) was traveling in manual mode westbound on Euclid Avenue in San Francisco when it was involved in a collision. Address: Jones Street at Ellis Street, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94102
ExtText: A Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) was traveling in manual mode southbound on Jones Street at Ellis Street in San Francisco when a cyclist fell while passing between the Waymo AV and another vehicle. As the cyclist attempted to overtake the Waymo AV and was in turn being overtaken by the adjacent passenger vehicle, the cyclist fell between the two vehicles. As the bicycle was falling, the bicycle’s front tire appears to have made contact with the rear driver’s side wheel of the Waymo AV, and the cyclist appears to have made contact with the side of the other passenger vehicle in the left adjacent lane. The Waymo AV sustained no damage. The passenger vehicle did not stop and left the scene. The cyclist was transported from the scene and reportedly treated for potential head injuries.

Address: Laguna Street at Vallejo Street, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94123

Address: HARRISON & 1 ST, SAN FRANCISCO, SAN FRANCISCO, CA, 94107
ExtText:

There are no known injuries, and Lyft does not know what (if any) damage was sustained by the Toyota. 

*Note: this lane merges onto a freeway ramp and may not have provided a place to safely pull over.

Address: 700 Blk Baker St, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94115
ExtText: A Cruise autonomous vehicle (“Cruise AV”), was in autonomous mode and traveling westbound on McAllister Street near Baker Street. Address: Shrader Street at Haight Street, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94117
ExtText: A Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) was traveling northbound on Shrader Street at Haight Street in San Francisco when it was involved in a collision. When the passenger vehicle began to make a left turn in front of the Waymo AV from westbound Haight Street onto southbound Shrader Street, the Waymo AV test driver stopped the Waymo AV. A passenger vehicle behind the Waymo AV then made contact with the stationary Waymo AV’s rear bumper at approximately 5 MPH. The Waymo AV sustained minor damage to its rear bumper, and the passenger vehicle sustained minor damage to its front bumper. No injuries were reported.

Address: Milmont Dr. / Dixon Landing Rd., Milpitas , Santa Clara, CA, 95035
ExtText: The Pony.ai autonomous vehicle ("Pony.ai AV") was stopped for approximately 3 minutes at the red light in the far right lane on Milmont Dr. preparing to turn right onto Dixon Landing Rd. In front of the Pony.ai AV are several other vehicles also preparing to turn right. While stopped, Vehicle 2 came up quickly immediately behind the Pony.ai AV then proceeded to stop abruptly. Vehicle 2 then proceeds to creep up towards the Pony.ai with the driver of Vehicle 2 appearing to look down. Vehicle 2 then lurches forward quickly towards the Pony.ai AV. The Pony.ai AV operator proceeded to disengage from autonomous mode to attempt to avoid an accident, however, as the Pony.ai AV vehicle operator attempted to step on the throttle, the Pony.ai AV is rear-ended by Vehicle 2. The Pony.ai AV was stopped at 0 mph, while the approximate speed of Vehicle 2 at the point of collision was 5 mph. The Pony.ai AV operator noted that prior to the collision, the driver of Vehicle 2 appeared to drive erratically across other intersections as well. The contact between the vehicles caused a moderate damage to the back of the Pony.ai AV and moderate damage to Vehicle 2. Both drivers pulled over to the side of the roadway and exchanged information. There were no injuries reported and the police were not called. Pursuant to protocol, Pony.ai ran simulations after the accident to determine if the ADV would have reacted differently. The results indicate the Pony.ai ADV would not have reacted differently.

Address: Green near Columbus, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94113

Address: 1011 De Haro St, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94107
ExtText: A Cruise autonomous vehicle (“Cruise AV”), was in autonomous mode and traveling northbound on De Haro Street between 23rd and 22nd streets. The AVTO, concerned for their safety, disengaged from autonomous mode to attempt to move the AV around the pedestrian who was still rapidly heading directly towards the AV in the center of the street. The Cruise AV was then struck by a skateboarder that suddenly entered the crosswalk from the southeast sidewalk, coming downhill from 22nd street. Contact was made by the skateboarder to the Cruise AV. This caused damage to the front quarter panel area and the articulating radar of the Cruise AV. Because the skateboarder appeared injured, 911 was immediately called. The skateboarder left the scene shortly after the incident and before the police arrived. The Cruise AVTOs remained on the scene and gave a statement to the police.

Address: Precita Avenue at Cesar Chavez, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94110
ExtText: A Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) was traveling eastbound on Precita Avenue and yielding to traffic while preparing to merge onto Cesar Chavez in San Francisco when it was involved in a collision. AV steered away from the cyclist, but the cyclist continued into the lane and the bicycle's left handlebar made contact with the Argo
AV's passenger side door handle. The Test Specialist brought the AV to a stop. The cyclist maintained balance, continued to cross
the lanes behind the stopped Argo AV, and left the scene after a brief conversation with the left seat Test Specialist, during which the
cyclist indicated that he was fine and apologized. The Argo AV sustained minor damage to its passenger side door handle.

On July 24, 2022 at 11:16 AM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a van on Connecticut Street north of 25th Street.

While proceeding northwest on Connecticut Street in autonomous mode, the Waymo AV came to a stop behind a stalled bus blocking the roadway. The driver transitioned the system to manual mode and began to reverse out of the narrow road. While reversing, a van approached from behind and the Waymo AV made contact with the front left fender of the van. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was not engaged and a test driver was operating the Waymo AV in manual mode. The Waymo AV sustained minor damage.

Address: 700 Parnassus Ave, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94122

The driver of the Toyota FJ Cruiser left the scene without exchanging information. There were no injuries and a police report was later filed.

Address: 3597 Mission St, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94110

driver of the Hyundai Elantra left the scene without exchanging information. There were no injuries and a police report was later filed.

The Waymo AV was stopped in the dedicated left turn lane facing north on the Embarcadero, awaiting a green signal for a protected left turn onto Broadway. The signal for traffic proceeding north on the Embarcadero turned green, and traffic in adjacent lanes began moving. The left turn arrow signal for the dedicated turn lane occupied by the Waymo AV remained red. The passenger car that had been stopped directly behind the Waymo AV began moving forward. The front of the passenger car made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV, immediately after which the passenger car left the scene.

At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV sustained minor damage and the Waymo AV test driver reported lower back pain.

Address: 698 Spruce Street, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94118
ExtText:
A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV") operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling eastbound on Geary Boulevard
toward the intersection with Spruce Street. As it approached the intersection, the Cruise AV entered the left hand turn lane, turned the left
turn signal on, and initiated a left turn on a green light onto Spruce Street. At the same time, a Toyota Prius traveling westbound in the
rightmost bus and turn lane of Geary Boulevard approached the intersection in the right turn lane. The Toyota Prius was traveling
approximately 40 mph in a 25 mph speed zone. The Cruise AV came to a stop before fully completing its turn onto Spruce Street due to the
oncoming Toyota Prius, and the Toyota Prius entered the intersection traveling straight from the turn lane instead of turning. Shortly
thereafter, the Toyota Prius made contact with the rear passenger side of the Cruise AV. The impact caused damage to the right rear door,
panel, and wheel of the Cruise AV. Police and Emergency Medical Services were called to the scene, and a police report was filed. The
Cruise AV was towed from the scene. Occupants of both vehicles received medical treatment for allegedly minor injuries.

Address: 1534 Hayes St, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94117

Lyon Street and Baker Street when a pedestrian ran in front of the AV. The Cruise AV stopped for the pedestrian and, moments later, the
pedestrian began yelling and approaching the Cruise AV. The Cruise AV operator disengaged the Cruise AV from autonomous mode to
leave the scene. The Cruise AV operator drove the vehicle forward and maneuvered away from the pedestrian, but the pedestrian
continued to approach the Cruise AV and jumped onto the hood of the Cruise AV. The pedestrian fell in front of the Cruise AV and
remained there until later fleeing the scene. The injury status of the pedestrian is unknown and a police report was filed.

Address: 900 Villa St., Mountain View, Santa Clara, CA, 94041
ExtText: A registered Ghost AV Test vehicle was hit by crash debris while traveling on I-680 N. The Ghost vehicle neither hit nor was hit by another vehicle. The Ghost car was traveling in AV mode with a registered AV Test Driver behind the wheel and an additional Safety Co-Driver in the passenger seat. Traffic slowed quickly due to a crash ahead of the Ghost car. Consistent with their training, the Ghost driver took control by braking and disengaging the autonomous system. The Ghost car stopped without impacting the preceding car. A Mercedes car immediately following the Ghost car also came to a stop without impacting the Ghost car. Ghost's understanding based on communications at the scene is that a Grand Cherokee traveling behind the Mercedes tried to swerve to avoid impacting the Mercedes but clipped the Mercedes and rolled over. To Ghost's knowledge, nobody in the Grand Cherokee was injured. On April 30, 2023 at 1:53 PM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving an SUV on Oak Street at Octavia Boulevard. 

While the Waymo AV was parked at the right side curb of the road on Oak Street, an SUV that was passing the parked Waymo AV in the rightmost lane made contact with the rear driver’s side of the Waymo AV. Address: 25th St & Sanchez St, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94114
ExtText: The Waymo AV was traveling east on 25th Street between Sanchez Street and Vicksburg Street when it approached an SUV that was stopped in the lane in front of the Waymo AV. The Waymo AV began passing the stopped SUV on the left when the SUV began reversing in the lane. The Waymo AV then stopped behind and to the left of the SUV, and the SUV continued reversing and began a turning maneuver to enter a parking space. The left side of the SUV made contact with the front right corner of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV was stopped and the AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Both vehicles sustained damage.

Address: San Thomas Expressway & Central Expressway, SANTA CLARA, SANTA CLARA, CA, 95051
ExtText: The Mercedes-Benz was leaving the off-ramp of EB Central Expressway and approached the merge at NB San Thomas Expressway. The driver yielded to cross traffic at the merge when the Porsche Cayenne vehicle rear-ended the Mercedes-Benz.

Address: Bay St and Columbus Ave, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94133
ExtText: On Monday May 1st at 11:41am a Weride autonomous vehicle (Vehicle 1) was in Autonomous Mode stopped at the intersection of Bay St towards Columbus Ave appropriately yielding to a illegally U turning skateboard on Bay St North to South direction in front of the AV (Vehicle 1). While yielding, a bicyclist was coming from behind our AV (Vehicle 1) head was turned left possibly looking for cross traffic. When the cyclist turned his head forward, it was too late to react in time to our stopped vehicle(Vehicle 1) with the given distance and speed they were traveling at in which the cyclist collided with our vehicle (Vehicle 1). Our Weride safety officer immediately disengaged and hand signaled to the bicyclist to pull over to the closest safe place to park as to not obstruct traffic. As our safety officer parked and got out of the car to check on the bicyclist, the bicyclist was already on in motion on his bicycle and "fist bumped" our safety officer while passing by him and leaving the scene without exchanging any information.

Address: 887 Geary St, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94109

The parties exchanged information. The Cruise AV operator in the Cruise AV later reported head, shoulder and back injuries.

Address: Wilshire Boulevard at 26th Street, Santa Monica, Los Angeles, CA, 90403

Address: Kearny Street and Commercial Street Intersection, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94108
ExtText: A Zoox vehicle in autonomy was proceeding northbound on Kearny Street in stop-and-go traffic through an active construction zone. At the same time, an e-scooter traveling near the right curb was passing other slow traffic behind the Zoox vehicle. Before the e-scooter could also pass the Zoox vehicle on the right, the e-scooter weaved away from the curb, seemingly to avoid a drainage grate, and came within a close following distance behind the Zoox vehicle. As the Zoox vehicle came to a stop again for traffic ahead the e-scooter rider did not stop, and the e-scooter made contact with the right rear tail light of the Zoox vehicle. The e-scooter rider remained upright, did not stop to exchange information, and immediately rode off while the Zoox vehicle was still stopped. There were no injuries and police were not called. The damage to the Zoox vehicle was limited to a cracked tail light lens.

Address: Potrero Avenue at 21st Street, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94110
ExtText:

The Waymo AV was traveling southbound on Potrero Avenue in the leftmost lane as it was approaching the intersection with 21st Street. The signal for traffic proceeding south on Potrero Avenue was green for the Waymo AV as it approached the intersection. As the Waymo AV approached, an individual riding a motorized scooter traveling north on Potrero Avenue proceeded to turn left onto westbound 21st Street, across the paths of the Waymo AV and other oncoming vehicles. The Waymo AV began to brake, and the Waymo AV test driver transitioned to manual mode and brought the Waymo AV to a stop. A passenger car traveling directly behind the Waymo AV then made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. The individual riding the scooter was not contacted by the Waymo AV or any other vehicle. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was not engaged and a test driver was operating the Waymo AV in manual mode. Both the Waymo AV and the passenger car sustained damage, and the individual on the motorized scooter left the scene.

Address: Jack London Alley at Varney Place, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94107

Address: 1695 Polk Street, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94109
ExtText: A Cruise autonomous vehicle ("Cruise AV"), operating in driverless autonomous mode, was traveling southbound on Polk Street near the intersection with Clay Street. During the time that the power cable was being cleared and that the Cruise AV was stopped, the Cruise AV ran low on battery power and did not have enough power to return to Cruise facilities on its own. The Cruise AV was therefore towed from the scene once the power cables were cleared.

Address: 405FWY SOUTH, GARDENA, LOS ANGELES, CA, 90248
ExtText: The subject Mercedes-Benz vehicle was driving in stop and go traffic on the 405 south freeway in Gardena, California with the L3 ADS activated. The test route selected by the driver in the vehicle's navigation system indicated an upcoming exit, so the driver began to prepare for a lane change towards the highway exit by deactivating the L3 ADS and activating the turn signal. Once the vehicle was in conventional driving mode, the driver looked for a gap in the adjacent lane to merge towards the exit lane, applied the brakes, and slowed the vehicle down. The SUV following the Mercedes-Benz vehicle did not respond in time to the vehicle's braking and contacted the rear of the Mercedes-Benz approximately 10 seconds after the L3 ADS was deactivated.  The Mercedes-Benz vehicle experienced minor damage to the rear bumper. No injuries were reported, no airbags deployed in either vehicle, and both vehicles were driven from the scene of the incident.

Address: 605N HWY , SANTA FE SPRINGS, LOS ANGELES, CA, 90650
ExtText: The subject Mercedes-Benz DRIVE PILOT test vehicle was traveling between 15 – 20 mph in the #2 northbound lane on the 605 Freeway in California in stop and go traffic with the L3 ADS activated by the driver. The vehicle’s ADS determined that a truck traveling in the adjacent lane had a trajectory towards the Drive Pilot’s lane, and so the Mercedes-Benz test vehicle autonomously applied the brakes to avoid a collision.  After applying the brakes and bringing itself to a standstill, the Mercedes-Benz was then struck in the rear bumper by a trailing semi-truck that did not stop in time.  No injuries were reported, no airbags deployed in either vehicle, and both vehicles were able to be driven from the scene of the incident. The Mercedes-Benz vehicle experienced minor damage to the rear bumper, and no damage was observed on the semi-truck at the scene. The CA Traffic Collision Report for the subject incident noted a violation of California Vehicle Code 22350 (unsafe speed for traffic conditions) by the semi-truck in the #2 lane that struck the rear bumper of the Mercedes-Benz.

Address: Intersection of 11th and Bryant St, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94103
ExtText: A Zoox vehicle (Vehicle 1) in autonomy was stopped at a red light in the right travel lane on southbound 11th Street at the intersection with Bryant/Division Streets in San Francisco. After the light turned green, the Zoox vehicle entered the intersection and began bearing right onto southbound Bryant Street when a lane-splitting motorcycle (Vehicle 2) operator maneuvered around other traffic and quickly came up on the rear of the Zoox vehicle, traversing laterally in lane from the left to the right side of the Zoox vehicle. The Zoox vehicle braked and then the Zoox vehicle operator disengaged. The motorcycle then struck the passenger’s side of the rear bumper and quarter panel on the Zoox vehicle and the motorcycle and its operator fell to the ground. The motorcycle operator appeared to have scraped his hands, but declined medical attention. The motorcycle sustained minor damage to the fairing, left side mirror, and front and rear left turn signal lens and the Zoox vehicle did not sustain damage. The motorcycle operator left the scene without exchanging their information. The police were not called.

Address: Lakeview Blvd & Gateway Blvd, Fremont, Alameda, CA, 94538
ExtText: On April 23, 2024, a Pony.ai autonomous vehicle (AV) scraped a curb on Lakeview Blvd near the intersection of Lakeview Blvd & Gateway Blvd in Fremont, CA. The vehicle was operating in supervised autonomous ("Drivered") mode. There were no other vehicles, pedestrians, or road users involved.Following the incident, the safety operator promptly drove the AV, in manual mode, to Pony.ai's Fremont office. There were no injuriesreported, and the police were not called.

Address: On Folsom St at 21st St, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94110
ExtText: A Zoox vehicle, operating in manual mode, was traveling north on Folsom Street, preparing to turn left onto 21st Street in San Francisco when the front wheel on the driver's side rode over a traffic island to the left side of the Zoox vehicle. The sidewall of the tire was damaged as a result of the interaction. There were no reported injuries and the police were not called.

Address: Bayshore Boulevard at Boutwell Street, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94124
ExtText: On April 13, 2024 at 3:35 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a pickup truck on Bayshore Boulevard near Boutwell Street. The Waymo AV was traveling southbound on Bayshore Boulevard in the far right lane when it passed a pickup truck that was stopped in the bike lane. As the Waymo passed the pickup truck, the driver of the pickup truck opened the driver’s side door and the door made contact with the Waymo’s passenger side wing mirror and rear right sensor housing.  At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver's seating position). The Waymo AV sustained damage.

Address: Vallejo Street at Stockton Street, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94133
ExtText: On April 11, 2024 at 10:14 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a heavy truck on Vallejo Street at Stockton Street. The Waymo AV was traveling westbound on Vallejo Street and stopped at a red light.  The heavy truck was turning left onto Vallejo Street from Stockton Street when the left side of the heavy truck made contact with the driver side front corner of the Waymo AV.  The heavy truck left the scene. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver's seating position).  The Waymo AV sustained damage.

Address: 3rd Avenue toward Foster City Blvd, Foster City, San Mateo, CA, 94404
ExtText: A Zoox vehicle in autonomy, traveling westbound on 3rd Avenue toward Foster City Blvd in Foster City drove over an in-lane utility valve box with a displaced valve cover. The Zoox vehicle sustained damage to the undercarriage. There were no reported injuries and police were not called.

Address: Jerrold Avenue at Barneveld Avenue, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94124
ExtText: On March 30, 2024 at 1:33 AM PT, a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving an SUV on Jerrold Avenue at Barneveld Avenue.The Waymo AV was stopped at a stop sign on Jerrold Avenue and yielding to a pickup truck that was in the intersection making a left turnfrom Barneveld Avenue onto Jerrold Avenue when the front right corner of the SUV, which was traveling behind the Waymo AV, madecontact with the rear left corner of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomousmode. Both vehicles sustained damage.

Address: Louisiana Avenue at Kerwood Avenue, Los Angeles, Los Angeles, CA, 90025
ExtText: On March 28, 2024 at 7:30 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in Los Angeles, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on Louisiana Avenue at Kerwood Avenue. While making a tight left turn from southbound Kerwood Avenue onto northeastbound Louisiana Avenue, the Waymo AV made contact with the driver side of a parked passenger car. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). Both vehicles sustained damage.

Address: Church Street at Market Street, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94114
ExtText: On March 22, 2024 at 10:00 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car near the 200 block of Church Street before Market Street. The Waymo AV was traveling north on Church Street towards the intersection with Market Street when it came to a stop behind an SUV which was stopped in-lane to load passengers. Another SUV approached from behind the Waymo AV and came to a stop. The lead SUV finished loading passengers and proceeded forward to the stop line at Market Street, and the Waymo AV proceeded forward as well. The trailing SUV proceeded forward and the front of the SUV made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV.  At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage and the SUV left the scene.

Address: Division Street at 9th Street, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94103
ExtText: On March 19, 2024 at 7:18 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on Division Street at 9th Street. The Waymo AV was traveling west on Division Street after having stopped at the stop sign at Vermont Street and was approaching the intersection with 9th Street when a passenger car approached from behind the Waymo AV, ran the stop sign at Vermont Street, and made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. The front of the passenger car made continuous contact with the rear of the Waymo AV while both vehicles were still in motion for a short period of time before the passenger car slowed down and separated from the AV. The Waymo AV proceeded through the intersection with 9th Street and came to a stop on Division Street west of the intersection with 9th Street. The passenger car then accelerated and the front right corner of the passenger car made contact with the rear left corner of the stationary Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Both vehicles sustained damage.

Address: On 3rd Avenue at S Norfolk St, San Mateo, San Mateo, CA, 94401
ExtText: A Zoox vehicle (Vehicle 1), operating in manual mode, was traveling northeast on 3rd Avenue toward Norfolk St in San Mateo. The Zoox vehicle was stopped in the right through lane behind traffic for a red traffic signal, when it was rear ended by a passenger car (Vehicle 2) that was traveling directly behind. There was no visible damage to either vehicle and the police were not called. The safety operator of the Zoox vehicle reported back pain a few days after the collision. Zoox vehicle camera footage shows that the driver of the passenger car may not have been looking ahead at the roadway prior to and at the time of contact.

Address: S Figueroa Street at 7th Street, Los Angeles, Los Angeles, CA, 90017
ExtText: On March 14, 2024 at 2:42 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in Los Angeles, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on S Figueroa Street at 7th Street. The Waymo AV was traveling northeast on S Figueroa Street in the lane adjacent to the rightmost, bus-only lane. As the Waymo AV approached the intersection with 7th Street, it came to a stop behind another vehicle stopped in traffic. As a passenger car was passing the Waymo AV in the bus lane to the right of the Waymo AV, the passenger car made contact with the passenger side of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage and the passenger car left the scene.Waymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 2 of Standing General Order 2021-01.

Address: Intersection of Thompson Ave. and Alvin Street, Mountain View, Santa Clara, CA, 94043

The Prius vehicle bumped the medium and knocked over a white pylon. The vehicle had minor damage and no injuries were reported. No other vehicles or VRUs were involved. Address: S Figueroa Street at Venice Boulevard, Los Angeles, Los Angeles, CA, 90015
ExtText: On March 8, 2024 at 12:06 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in Los Angeles, California was in a collision involving a passenger car near the 1600 block of S. Figueroa Street. The Waymo AV made a left turn from W. 17th Street onto S. Figueroa Street and came to a stop in a queue of stopped traffic. A passenger car traveling straight on S. Figueroa Street behind the Waymo AV made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV.  At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Address: 2323 Cesar Chavez Street, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94124
ExtText: On March 3, 2024 at 3:12 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a pick-up truck near the 2300 block of Cesar Chavez Street.The Waymo AV was traveling westbound on Cesar Chavez Street towards 26th Street when it approached a pick-up truck which was oriented with its rear partially in the roadway on the north side of Cesar Chavez street. The pick-up truck was stationary but its reverse lights were illuminated. The Waymo AV came to a stop momentarily to yield to the pick-up truck, then began moving again to pass the pick-up truck, which had remained stopped. After the Waymo AV started moving, the pick-up truck began reversing further out of the driveway and the rear of the pick-up truck made contact with the right side of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). Both vehicles sustained damage.

Address: Odd Fellows Way and 7th Street, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94103
ExtText: On March 2, 2024 at 8:14 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a dumpster on Odd Fellows Way, at the rear garage exit of 1155 Market Street. The Waymo AV was making a reversing right turn out of the parking garage onto Odd Fellows Way when the rear left corner of the Waymo AV made contact with a dumpster which was next to the curb in the roadway opposite the garage exit.  At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was not engaged and a test driver was operating the Waymo AV in manual mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage.

Address: On Mission St at 9th St, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94103
ExtText: A Zoox vehicle (Vehicle 1) in autonomy, traveling northeast on Mission St, was stopped in lane for a red traffic light at 9th Street. A SamTrans bus (Vehicle 2), with a front-mounted triple-bike rack extending past the width of the bus on the driver's side, was traveling southeast on 9th Street and attempting a right turn onto Mission St. The protruding edge of the bike rack was encroaching into the Zoox vehicle's travel lane as the bus was executing the right hand turn. As the light turned green the Zoox vehicle inched forward and attempted to steer away from the bus. Just as the safety operator disengaged from autonomy, the protruding edge of the bike rack made contact with the driver's side fender on the Zoox vehicle. There were no reported injuries and the police were not called.

Address: Harrison and 13th Street, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94103
ExtText: A Zoox vehicle (Vehicle 1) in autonomy was traveling southwest on Harrison St and turning right onto 13th Street on a green traffic signal. While executing the turn, the Zoox vehicle braked to achieve a minimal risk condition due to an unexpected system fault, the safety operator disengaged, and then was rear ended by a passenger car (Vehicle 2) that was also turning directly behind the Zoox vehicle. The rear bumper cover and rear radar unit on the Zoox vehicle sustained damage. The hood, front grille and front bumper cover on the passenger car appeared to have sustained damage. There were no reported injuries and police were not called.

Address: The Embarcadero at Washington Street, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94111
ExtText: On February 18, 2024 at 1:03 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on The Embarcadero at Washington Street.The Waymo AV was stopped in traffic for a red light on The Embarcadero southbound when a passenger car approached from behind and made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver's seating position). Both vehicles sustained damage and the passenger car left the scene.

Address: US 101N at Ellis St Exit, Sunnyvale, Santa Clara, CA, 94089
ExtText: On February 15th, a test vehicle operating with the automated driving system engaged was traveling Northbound on Highway 101 in Sunnyvale. Address: Watt Way and West Exposition Boulevard, Los Angeles, Los Angeles, CA, 90089
ExtText: On February 5, 2024 at 10:01 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in Los Angeles, California was in a collision involving a gate at Watt Way and West Exposition Boulevard.The Waymo AV was traveling south on Watt when it approached an automatic gate as it had started to close. Address: Potrero Avenue near 22nd Street, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94110
ExtText: On January 31, 2024 at 5:15 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger vehicle on Potrero Avenue near 22nd Street.The Waymo AV was traveling southbound on Potrero Avenue in the leftmost thru lane, adjacent to a dedicated left turn lane on its left. The passenger vehicle behind the Waymo AV then attempted to change lanes into the dedicated left turn lane, and made contact with the rear driver side corner of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Both vehicles sustained damage.

Address: Intersection of Boyce Ave and Fife Ave, Palo Alto, Santa Clara, CA, 94301
ExtText: On Wednesday, January 31st at approximately 4:20pm, a Nuro Prius was operating in autonomous mode driving south on Boyce Ave in Palo Alto. Address: I-580E and I-238 Junction, Castro Valley, Alameda, CA, 94546
ExtText: On January 26th, a test vehicle operating with the automated driving system engaged was traveling Eastbound on Interstate 580 in Castro Valley when a nearby semi-trailer truck merging from Interstate 238 generated a draft that projected road debris onto the test vehicle. Address: On 2nd St Left turn to  E San Fernando St, San Jose, Santa Clara, CA, 95134
ExtText: At approximately 12:56pm, a WeRide vehicle (car 1) was slowing to a stop (< 3mph) on 2nd street at the intersection of East San Fernando st. to turn left in an effort to yield to crossing pedestrians. Address: On Stockton St near Union St, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94133
ExtText: A Zoox vehicle (Vehicle 1) in autonomy was traveling on southbound Stockton St near Union St in San Francisco. Address: Cross street: Terra Bella and Shoreline, Mountain View, Santa Clara, CA, 94043
ExtText: On Friday, January 12th, a Nuro Prius operating autonomously was stopped at a red light at the intersection of Shoreline and Terra Bella Ave. A Mazda approaching the intersection failed to completely stop and rear-ended the Nuro Prius. No injuries were reported. Both vehicles sustained minor damage.

Address: On Florida St near the intersection with Division St, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94103
ExtText: A Zoox vehicle (Vehicle 1), operating in manual mode, was traveling southbound on Florida St near the intersection with Division St in San Francisco. The Zoox vehicle slowed to a stop to allow an oncoming box truck (Vehicle 2), attempting to turn left, to clear when the box truck made contact with the driver's side rear camera housing on the Zoox vehicle. Address: On Bryant St at the intersection with 6th St, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94103
ExtText: A Zoox vehicle (Vehicle 1), operating in manual mode, was stopped for a red traffic light  on northbound Bryant St at the intersection with 6th St in San Francisco with an SUV (Vehicle 2) traveling directly behind . As the signal turned green the Zoox vehicle remained stopped to avoid blocking the intersection as traffic was still stopped ahead. The SUV proceeded to move into the adjacent left lane, when its front bumper on the passenger's side made contact with the driver's side rear bumper of the Zoox vehicle. The front bumper of the SUV appeared to have sustained minor damage. The driver of the SUV left the scene without exchanging information. There were no reported injuries and the police were not called.

Address: HWY 17 Northbound near Hamman Park, San Jose, Santa Clara, CA, 95128
ExtText: A Ghost ADS-equipped car was driving engaged Northbound on Highway 17. As always, there were two safety drivers in the car. Traffic was moving in all four lanes at or near the speed limit. The Ghost vehicle was in the right-middle lane. Another vehicle (the "lead" car) entered into the Ghost car's lane from the right. While there were numerous vehicles ahead of the Ghost car before that vehicle entered the lane, the lead vehicle blocked the view of the lane before it. Throughout the incident, traffic in the other three lanes continued at a steady pace. When the lead vehicle entered into the lane ahead of the Ghost car, the Ghost car applied the brakes to accommodate the intrusion and then continued to match the speed of the lead car. The lead car suddenly slammed the brakes. The Ghost car followed suit, reducing its speed from 19 mps (42.5 mph) to 4.7 mps (10.5 mph) within the next three seconds. The Ghost car was able to match the rapid speed reduction of the lead car and avoid contact. The driver following the Ghost car was not able to respond as quickly as the Ghost ADS. When the following driver began to apply the brakes, the car was about five meters behind and was traveling at 6.5 mps. At the point of impact, the Ghost vehicle was traveling at 4.78 mps (10.7 mph), matching the lead car. There were no injuries. The vehicles suffered only cosmetic damage, the drivers exchanged information, and the Ghost safety drivers returned to home base in conventional mode.

Address: Manhattan Place at West Adams Boulevard, Los Angeles, Los Angeles, CA, 90018
ExtText: On January 8, 2023 at 12:05 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in Los Angeles, California was in a collision involving an SUV on Manhattan Place at West Adams Boulevard.  The Waymo AV was traveling northbound on Manhattan Place when it came to a stop to yield to an oncoming vehicle in a narrow roadway with parked vehicles on both sides of the street. As the oncoming SUV passed the Waymo AV, the driver’s side rear of the SUV made contact with the driver’s side rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage and the SUV left the scene.

Address: On Capp Street at 24th Street, San Francisco, San Francisco, CA, 94110
ExtText: A Zoox vehicle (Vehicle 1) in autonomy was stopped at a red traffic light on northbound Capp St at the intersection with 24th St in San Francisco. At that time, an SUV (Vehicle 2), heading southbound on Capp St, failed to stop for the red traffic light and entered the intersection, causing a collision with a passenger car (Vehicle 3) that was traveling eastbound on 24th Street. The SUV spun after making contact with the passenger car and collided with the stopped Zoox vehicle, damaging the front bumper on the driver’s side and driver’s side fender, mirror, and sensors on the Zoox vehicle. The police and EMS personnel were called to the scene. The driver of the SUV left the scene without exchanging information. The passenger car appeared to sustain significant damage to the front end. There were no reported injuries.
